---
import ApplicationLayout from '../../layouts/ApplicationLayout.astro';

const title = "Used Motor Oil Centrifuge Applications";
const description = "Centrifuge systems for waste oil recovery, used oil re-refining, and black diesel cleaning. Industrial oil purification solutions from Dolphin Centrifuge.";

const jsonLd = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "CollectionPage",
  "name": title,
  "description": description,
  "url": "https://dolphincentrifuge.com/applications/used-motor-oil/",
  "publisher": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "Dolphin Centrifuge", "url": "https://dolphincentrifuge.com" },
};

const toc = [
  { id: "why-centrifuges-for-used-motor-oil", label: "Why Centrifuges for Used Motor Oil" },
  { id: "waste-oil-recovery", label: "Waste Oil Recovery" },
  { id: "used-oil-re-refining", label: "Used Oil Re-Refining" },
  { id: "black-diesel-cleaning", label: "Black Diesel Cleaning" },
  { id: "general-oil-separation", label: "General Oil Separation" },
  { id: "choosing-the-right-system", label: "Choosing the Right System" },
];
---
<ApplicationLayout
  title={title}
  description={description}
  canonicalUrl="https://dolphincentrifuge.com/applications/used-motor-oil/"
  category="applications"
  categoryLabel="Used Motor Oil Applications"
  heroImage="/images/waste-oil-centrifuge/Industrial-Centrifuge-Systems-for-Waste-Oil.webp"
  heroImageAlt="Industrial centrifuge systems for waste oil recovery"
  toc={toc}
  relatedApplications={[
    { label: "Waste Oil Centrifuge", href: "/waste-oil-centrifuge/" },
    { label: "Lube Oil Centrifuge", href: "/lube-oil-centrifuge/" },
    { label: "Used Oil Re-Refining Centrifuge", href: "/used-oil-re-refining-plant-centrifuge/" },
  ]}
  relatedProducts={[
    { label: "DMPX-042 Disc Centrifuge", href: "/centrifuges/dmpx-042/" },
    { label: "DMPX-070 Disc Centrifuge", href: "/centrifuges/dmpx-070/" },
  ]}
  jsonLd={jsonLd}
>
  <article class="prose-dolphin max-w-none">
    <p>Our <a href="/disc-stack-centrifuge/">disc stack centrifuges</a> turn dirty waste oil into clean, sale-ready product. Whether you collect used motor oil, process black diesel, or re-refine industrial lubricants, Dolphin Centrifuge has a proven system for your operation.</p>

    <h2 id="why-centrifuges-for-used-motor-oil">Why Centrifuges for Used Motor Oil</h2>
    <p>Used motor oil contains water, sludge, metals, and carbon particles that must be removed before the oil can be sold, re-refined, or blended into fuel. Traditional filtration struggles with sub-micron contaminants and high volumes. <a href="/disc-stack-centrifuge/">Disc stack centrifuges</a> use up to 8,000 G-force to separate these contaminants continuously at flow rates of 10–60 GPM — far outperforming filters in both speed and cleanliness.</p>
    <p>Dolphin Centrifuge provides turnkey <a href="/centrifuge-systems/">centrifuge systems</a> that include heaters, feed pumps, piping, and controls — ready to plug into your existing process.</p>

    <h2 id="waste-oil-recovery">Waste Oil Recovery</h2>
    <p><strong>3-Phase Oil Recovery</strong> — Recover clean, sale-ready oil from collected waste oil streams. Our 3-phase disc stack centrifuges remove water, sludge, and metals down to 1 micron. Processing capacity ranges from 10 to 50 GPM depending on the centrifuge model selected.</p>
    <p>The <a href="/waste-oil-centrifuge/">waste oil centrifuge</a> application is the most popular configuration in our used motor oil lineup. Customers typically see payback in under 12 months through recovered oil sales.</p>

    <h2 id="used-oil-re-refining">Used Oil Re-Refining</h2>
    <p><strong>Re-Refining &amp; Fuel Blending</strong> — Process used motor oil, transmission fluid, and industrial lubricants for re-refining or fuel blending. The centrifuge removes ash, metals, and water to produce a clean feedstock.</p>
    <p>For dedicated re-refining operations, visit our <a href="/used-oil-re-refining-plant-centrifuge/">used oil re-refining centrifuge</a> page for detailed system specifications and process flow diagrams. Capacities range from 10 to 50 GPM.</p>

    <h2 id="black-diesel-cleaning">Black Diesel Cleaning</h2>
    <p><strong>Soot &amp; Carbon Removal</strong> — Clean black diesel and soot-laden fuels for reuse as burner fuel. Disc stack centrifuges remove carbon, water, and heavy contaminants at flow rates of 10–30 GPM.</p>
    <p>Learn more about our <a href="/black-diesel-centrifuge/">black diesel centrifuge</a> systems, which are specifically configured for high-carbon-content fuels.</p>

    <h2 id="general-oil-separation">General Oil Separation</h2>
    <p><strong>Versatile Oil Purification</strong> — Beyond motor oil, our centrifuges handle a wide range of petroleum and bio-based oils. Whether you need to purify, clarify, or polish oil at 5–60 GPM, Dolphin has a solution.</p>
    <p>See our full <a href="/oil-centrifuge/">oil centrifuge</a> overview for the complete range of oil separation applications we support.</p>

    <h2 id="choosing-the-right-system">Choosing the Right System</h2>
    <p>The right centrifuge depends on your feedstock, throughput requirements, and end-product specifications. Key factors include:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Flow rate</strong> — Match centrifuge capacity to your daily volume</li>
      <li><strong>Contaminant load</strong> — Heavy sludge requires a self-cleaning (SOPX/FOPX) bowl design</li>
      <li><strong>Water content</strong> — High water content calls for a 3-phase separator</li>
      <li><strong>End-product spec</strong> — Re-refining demands tighter separation than fuel blending</li>
    </ul>
    <p>Our engineers will help you select and size the right system. <a href="/contact-for-alfa-laval-centrifuges/">Contact us</a> for a free consultation, or call <strong>(248) 522-2573</strong> to speak with a specialist today.</p>
  </article>
</ApplicationLayout>
